A
teacher was shot and killed at Tsako village outside Tzaneen in Limpopo. It’s
alleged that lvone Mushwana (40) who is teacher at Nyatshiri Primary School, was
with her boyfriend next to a local scrap yard. Police
spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said people heard gun shots from where the
two were standing. Ngoepe
said they immediately went to investigate and they found lvone lying dead on
the ground and the boyfriend ran away and disappeared. "Within
few hours of hunting, the boyfriend aged 45, who is a local business man was
found dead in his house at Nkowankowa, with a gunshot wound and the firearm lying
next to his body," Ngoepe said. “The
Police in Letsitele have opened a case of murder following the death of the
female educator and in Ritavi, the police have opened a case of Inquest on the
death of the boyfriend,” He said. The
Provincial Commissioner Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba expressed his concern
about the domestic related incidents which are still prevalent in certain areas
of the province. 